). Jin’s army returned and camped in Yu, then attacked and annihilated it. They captured the **Yu King** (虞公) and his ministers, including **Bó** (伯), and used them to humiliate **Qín Mù Gōng** (秦穆公)’s daughter, who was sent as a **bride** (媵).

The **Hu Lord** (胡王) loved music, and the **Qin King** (秦穆公) enticed him with female musicians. According to the *Shiji*—**Qin Family History** (秦本纪)—
In the thirty-fourth year of **Qín Mù Gōng** (秦穆公), the **Róng King** (戎王) sent **Yóu Yú** (由余) to Qin.
